Etymology. The new species is named after Dr. Alexey Streltsov, Professor of Kaluga University in Russia , to whom we are much obliged for personal help and support during research as well as in everyday life. In particular, it was thanks to Alexey Streltsov that the long field trip to Laos by S.T. was possible. Distribution and Ecology. The species is known from many specimens, but only from the type locality in Bolaven Plateau, South Laos (
Fig. 4
). Almost all specimens were collected in montane forest by means of pifall traps baited with human dung.
